              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " After irradiation, the targets were",
                "dissolved in HCl; yttrium, strontium, and barium",
                "carriers were added and the solution was made",
                "strongly basic with NaOH to remove aluminum. After",
                "washing, the precipitate was dissolved in a small",
                "amount of concentrated HNO3, strontium and barium",
                "carriers were again added and then precipitated as",
                "nitrates with fuming nitric acid. The prepared",
                "samples were gamma counted as soon as possible flat",
                "against the aluminum shield of a NaI scintillation",
                "crystal. After a period of ten half-lives ( 32 h),",
                "the samples were beta counted with a lead shielded",
                "calibrated Geiger-Muller counter."
              ]
            }
          ],
